Storyboard For Moon And Earth Phases And Proton-Seconds!
Ian Beardsley Dec 21 2021!
The thinking process for development of ideas is interesting in itself. Here is seen what looks
much like a storyboard for brainstorming the ideas themselves. It is like writing pseudocode
when you are writing a program for the computer, an algorithm to achieve a desired end. You
write it using your own language. In python the print function is called print, in C it is printf; in
psuedocode you just use words of your own choice that represent the logic common to all
program languages, and then translate it into the language you want to use to compile it and
run it. For instance in your own pseudocode you might use input, if you translate it into C you
type printf() coupled with scanf(), if you do it in python you use name=raw_input(‘Enter your
name: ‘ ) to do it all in one phrase.!
On two (Page one is the title page) we see since the motions of the planets and moon are
circular, their phases are trigonometric, or given by a cosine wave.!
On pages three and four we see why the moon perfectly eclipses the sun, it has to do with the
moon’s radius, its distance from the earth, and the the sun’s radius and its distance from the
earth. Size is inversely proportional to distance.!
On pages ﬁve, six, and seven, we see how I derived the equation relating earth, moon, and sun
to the molar masses of gold and silver.!
